{"title_page": "Burwood, New Zealand", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2011}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n    |name                 = Burwood\n    |area_total_km2                 = 1.5900\n    |population_as_of                 = 2006\n    |population_total                 = 2868\n    |population_density_km2                 = auto\n  }}\n\n'''Burwood''' is a north-eastern suburb of [[Christchurch]], New Zealand. The suburb is mostly a residential area and is centred on [[Burwood Hospital]], [[Travis Wetland]] Nature Heritage Park and [[Bottle Lake Forest]] (a {{convert|31|acre|m2|adj=on}} recreation, forested area). Recently, the local [[iwi]], [[Ng\u0101i Tahu]], created a new subdivision in the area, naming it 'Tumara Park'.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ngaitahuproperty.co.nz/past-projects/tumara-park/# |title=Ng\u0101i Tahu Property \u2013 Tumara Park |access-date=31 March 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130612025211/http://www.ngaitahuproperty.co.nz/past-projects/tumara-park/# |archive-date=12 June 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nBurwood contains two schools: Burwood Primary School and [[Windsor School,New Zealand|Windsor School]].\n\nLarge areas of Burwood, including the Horseshoe Lake area, suffered severe damage in the [[2010 Canterbury earthquake|2010]] and [[2011 Christchurch earthquake]]s, and were abandoned under government policy that placed them in a [[residential red zone]].\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Burwood, New Zealand}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord|43|30|S|172|42|E|display=title|region:NZ_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n{{Christchurch City, New Zealand}}\n\n[[Category:Suburbs of Christchurch]]\n\n\n{{CanterburyNZ-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2011}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n    |name                 = Burwood\n    |area_total_km2                 = 1.5900\n    |population_as_of                 = 2006\n    |population_total                 = 2868\n    |population_density_km2                 = auto\n  }}\n\n'''Burwood''' is a north-eastern suburb of [[Christchurch]], New Zealand. The suburb is mostly a residential area and is centred on Burwood Hospital, [[Travis Wetland]] Nature Heritage Park and [[Bottle Lake Forest]] (a {{convert|31|acre|m2|adj=on}} recreation, forested area). Recently, the local [[iwi]], [[Ng\u0101i Tahu]], created a new subdivision in the area, naming it 'Tumara Park'.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ngaitahuproperty.co.nz/past-projects/tumara-park/# |title=Ng\u0101i Tahu Property - Tumara Park |access-date=31 March 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130612025211/http://www.ngaitahuproperty.co.nz/past-projects/tumara-park/# |archive-date=12 June 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nBurwood contains two schools: [[Burwood Primary School]] and [[Windsor School,New Zealand|Windsor School]].\n\nLarge areas of Burwood, including the Horseshoe Lake area, suffered severe damage in the [[2010 Canterbury Earthquake|2010]] and [[2011 Christchurch Earthquake]]s, and were abandoned under government policy that placed them in a [[residential red zone]].\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Burwood, New Zealand}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord|43|30|S|172|42|E|display=title|region:NZ_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n{{Christchurch City, New Zealand}}\n\n[[Category:Suburbs of Christchurch]]\n\n\n{{CanterburyNZ-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Schwede66", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixeddashesusing ascript; drop caps; the primary school isn't notable but the hospital is", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burwood,_New_Zealand"}
